The wait is 45 minutes, period point blank. Not 15-20 minutes. & They only take cash. They seem to lack organization and people in the back don’t wear masks and speak over the food which i don’t like but the food was okay I guess. The wait was not with the food though. FOOD: The mac and cheese had a lot of flavor and a tad bit too much cheese but that’s just my opinion. Everyone likes mac & cheese differently. The wings were soooooo good. I had sweet chili on the side, in my opinion it tastes better with the sauce on it but I only received 1 very small cup of sweet chili. The portions are really big, the chicken wings themselves were on the larger side which is a bit suspicious but I’ll say less. The fries were like regular frozen fries out of the package but they hit the next day when you reheat it, idk why. CUSTOMER SERVICE: The more mature lady at the front had the most welcoming and kind presence towards me and thanked me for my patience which I appreciated because I was lowkey catching an attitude for having to wait for so long. The other two younger ladies weren’t very welcoming. They remind me of teenage girls in highschool that the teacher pairs you with but they don’t really want to work with you but they just do it and get it over with. Overall, I wouldn’t recommend but I would try it again. Try it for yourself to see how you feel about it.

This reviews the location in Brooklyn NY in  zip code 11203.  For some reason I keep getting shown the Far Rockaway Silver Seafood & Chicken.  For a restaurant that's been opened a little more than 3mos.  Their order takers/cashiers aren't customer friendly.  One had a slight attitude on only my 3rd visit in as many months.  They seem to serve smaller portions and want to charge the same price as you would find at other surrounding seafood restaurants.  The taste of the food is good, a lot of Old Bay is used.  They need to be more generous with their portions and they will be up there competing with the likes of Fisherman's Cove and Sea King.
